,918,919,921,922,925],{},"Move ",[41,917,183],{}," and ",[41,920,409],{}," into a ",[41,923,924],{},"src"," folder:",[12,927,928],{},[15,929],{"alt":924,"src":930},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FGit\u002Fgh-paegs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-05-30%2010.13.50.png",[12,932,933],{},"Back in your terminal, run:",[65,935,937],{"className":479,"code":936,"language":481,"meta":71,"style":71},"npm run deploy\n",[41,938,939],{"__ignoreMap":71},[193,940,941,943,946],{"class":195,"line":196},[193,942,617],{"class":488},[193,944,945],{"class":228}," run",[193,947,948],{"class":228}," deploy\n",[12,950,951,952,955],{},"When you see ",[41,953,954],{},"Published"," in the terminal, you're deployed.",[12,957,958],{},[15,959],{"alt":954,"src":960},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FGit\u002Fgh-paegs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-05-30%2010.14.47.png",[12,962,963],{},"Head to your GitHub repo — you'll see a new gh-pages branch:",[12,965,966],{},[15,967],{"alt":17,"src":968},"https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FGit\u002Fgh-paegs\u002F%E6%88%AA%E5%9C%96%202023-05-30%2010.16.03.png",[12,970,971,972,974,975,93],{},"And the site is now live at ",[41,973,43],{}," — in this example, ",[41,976,977],{},"https:\u002F\u002Fhsiangfeng.github.io\u002Fexample-gh-pages",[75,979,980],{"title":77,"type":78},[12,981,982],{},"GitHub auto-detects the gh-pages branch — if it exists, it deploys. The deploy process shows up in the repo's Actions tab under \"pages build and deployment\". Once it turns green, you're deployed.",[12,984,985,986,988,989,992,993,995,996,999,1000,1002,1003,93],{},"Quick aside on how gh-pages works under the hood: in ",[41,987,669],{}," we added ",[41,990,991],{},"gh-pages -d src",". That tells gh-pages to push the contents of the ",[41,994,924],{}," folder to the gh-pages branch. The ",[41,997,998],{},"-d"," flag is short for directory — it specifies which folder to push. Without ",[41,1001,998],{},", it defaults to the root, but you don't want to push everything (including node_modules) so we specify ",[41,1004,924],{},[12,1006,1007,1008,1011],{},"How does gh-pages know which repo to push to? It reads ",[41,1009,1010],{},".git","'s remote config — that's why we didn't have to specify a repo URL anywhere.",[75,1013,1014],{"title":77,"type":78},[12,1015,1016,1017,93],{},"If you're using CRA or Vite, read the gh-pages docs — they have specific config requirements, otherwise the site might not work. Check the ",[126,1018,1022],{"href":1019,"rel":1020},"https:\u002F\u002Fgithub.com\u002Ftschaub\u002Fgh-pages#github-pages-project-sites",[1021],"nofollow","official docs",[20,1024,1026],{"id":1025},"bonus","Bonus",[12,1028,1029,1030,1033,1034,1037],{},"If you're using Vite (or similar build tools), change ",[41,1031,1032],{},"\"deploy\": \"gh-pages -d dist\""," to ",[41,1035,1036],{},"\"deploy\": \"vite build && gh-pages -d dist\""," so it builds before deploying.",[1039,1040,1041],"style",{},"html pre.shiki code .s8XSl, html code.shiki .s8XSl{--shiki-light:#24292E;--shiki-default:#24292E;--shiki-dark:#F0F3F6}html pre.shiki code .syv7_, html code.shiki .syv7_{--shiki-light:#22863A;--shiki-default:#22863A;--shiki-dark:#72F088}html pre.shiki code .sK3KL, html code.shiki .sK3KL{--shiki-light:#6F42C1;--shiki-default:#6F42C1;--shiki-dark:#91CBFF}html pre.shiki code .sWayO, html code.shiki .sWayO{--shiki-light:#032F62;--shiki-default:#032F62;--shiki-dark:#ADDCFF}html .light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html.light .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-light);background: var(--shiki-light-bg);font-style: var(--shiki-light-font-style);font-weight: var(--shiki-light-font-weight);text-decoration: var(--shiki-light-text-decoration);}html .default .shiki span {color: var(--shiki-default);background: va